---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import More from "../components/More.tsx";
---

<Layout title="Count More">
  <main
    class="max-w-[768px] mx-3 md:mx-auto flex flex-row flex-wrap pt-12 font-cabinet font-bold"
  >
    <div class="w-full md:w-1/3 flex-shrink flex flex-col">
      <p class="text-2xl uppercase font-black pt-12 text-[18px] leading-[20px]">
        Make your vote
      </p>
      <h1
        class="text-7xl font-extrabold py-4 text-[75px] leading-[70.5px] tracking-tight"
      >
        Count<br />More
      </h1>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full md:w-2/3 flex flex-col space-y-8">
      <div class="border-4 mt-4 md:m-4 border-black p-4">
        <More client:load />
      </div>
      <div class="border-4 mt-4 md:m-4 border-transparent p-4">
        <p class="font-cabinet font-extrabold text-[24px]">
          Why does my vote count more in certain states?
        </p>
        <p class="font-satoshi font-medium text-[20px] leading-[30px] pt-4">
          There are many reasons that your vote can count "more" in one state
          over another.<br /><br />

          For the 2024 presidential election, we are most interested in
          so-called "battleground" states, where a small number of votes can
          legitimately swing the outcome of the election. In 2020, the key
          battlegrounds were Arizona, Florida, Georgia, Michigan, North
          Carolina, Pennsylvania and Wisconsin.<br /><br />

          Beyond battlegrounds, the <a
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Electoral_College"
            target="_blank"
            class="underline cursor-pointer hover:text-hover transition-colors duration-200"
            >Electoral College</a
          > system means that your vote counts more in states with fewer electoral
          votes per capita. For example, in 2024, Wyoming has 3 electoral votes and
          580,000 citizens, while California has 54 electoral votes and 39.3 million
          citizens. This means that a vote in Wyoming has roughly 3.7x the impact
          of a vote in California.<br /><br />

          <i>TODO</i>: update content.
        </p>
        <p class="font-cabinet font-extrabold text-[24px] pt-8">
          Who is Vote America?
        </p>
        <p class="font-satoshi font-medium text-[20px] leading-[30px] pt-4">
          <a
            href="https://www.voteamerica.com"
            target="_blank"
            class="underline cursor-pointer hover:text-hover transition-colors duration-200"
            >Vote America</a
          > is a nonprofit organization focused on strengthening American democracy
          by increasing voter turnout and removing barriers to voting. It was founded
          by Debra Cleaver, who previously launched Vote.org. The organization aims
          to boost voter turnout by assisting people with mail-in voting, especially
          in light of challenges such as the COVID-19 pandemic and various voting
          hurdles in the U.S.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- The mobile footer -->
      <div
        class="md:hidden flex flex-row py-12 border-4 border-transparent mt-4 md:m-4 p-4 items-baseline"
      >
        <div class="font-cabinet font-extrabold text-[18px] leading-[20px]">
          ©2024 Count More
        </div>
        <div class="flex-grow"></div>
        <a
          class="block font-cabinet font-extrabold text-[18px] leading-[20px] text-white bg-black rounded-md px-[20px] py-[14px] hover:bg-gray-700 transition-colors duration-200"
          href="mailto:Dave Peck <dave@frontseat.org>, Matt Lerner <matt@frontseat.org>?subject=Count%20More"
        >
          Contact</a
        >
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- the desktop footer -->
    <div
      class="hidden md:flex w-full flex-row py-12 border-4 border-transparent mt-4 md:m-4 p-4 items-baseline"
    >
      <div class="font-cabinet font-extrabold text-[18px] leading-[20px]">
        ©2024 Count More
      </div>
      <div class="flex-grow"></div>
      <a
        class="block font-cabinet font-extrabold text-[18px] leading-[20px] text-white bg-black rounded-md px-[20px] py-[14px] hover:bg-gray-700 transition-colors duration-200"
        href="mailto:Dave Peck <dave@frontseat.org>, Matt Lerner <matt@frontseat.org>?subject=Count%20More"
      >
        Contact</a
      >
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
